The Sitting 💊Antidote Part 4️⃣8️⃣ - LESS TYPING MORE #SMASHING 
Think about a twisted up towel: the tight and twisted part in the middle isn’t the problem but the consequence of what is happening around it. You have to work the ends to #fix the middle

Having a lacrosse ball or #foamroller at your #desk can go a long way to saving your #forearms. The key is to not just focus where there is tightness but #work the areas above and below the tight spots! This will provide good feedback to your nervous system and do a better job of releasing tension

Back the the rolled up towel: Most often the problem is NOT ONLY THE #MUSCLE. Muscles are usually tight because they are overworked and the nervous system is bombarding it with signals to “turn on and tighten up because there might be work to do”. Correct the core problem with the nervous system and voila - you have solved your problem. 
How do you know if you have a core problem with your nervous system —> get it checked!
